data.title: H Class Victorian Diesel Locomotives: MickFix Rail
data.text:
F202, formerly F311 and unofficially named 'Freddy', is currently undergoing an

overhaul. It is owned by Victrack Heritage and allocated to 707 Operations.

Last sighted 22nd June 2007 stabled, Seymour

Railway Heritage Centre stabling sheds. F208, formerly F317 and named 'Dynon Donk', has been painted in "707 Ops"

'black and red' livery and renumbered to it original state as F317.

It is owned by Victrack Heritage and allocated to 707 Operations.

Last sighted 18th March 2006 stabled, Steamrail open day Newport yard sidings. F211, formerly SEC3 and named 'Little Trimmer', has been repainted in "V/line" 'tangerine' livery.

It is owned by Victrack Heritage and allocated to the Australian Railway Historical Society (ARHS).

It is on static display in the Australian Railway Historical Society museum, Newport. This locomotive

features a plaque dedicating it to the many railway people who have maintained, serviced and operated locomotives. G511 now features "Watco's" 'black and yellow' livery

(not pictured). It is owned and operated by Watco Australia.

Last sighted 8th November 2012 Up Freight trailing C503, G514 and G513, leading

46 coal hoppers, passing over the Hunter River viaduct into Sandgate, Newcastle (NSW). G512 now features "Rail First Asset Management's" 'blue, grey and yellow' livery (not

pictured). It is owned by Rail First Asset Management and leased to QUBE Logistics.

Last sighted 24th October 2023 stabled latched behind

VL351, Qube Logistics intermodal terminal, Ultima. G513, named 'Mike Moy', now features "Southern Shorthaul Railroad's" 'black

and yellow' livery. It is owned and operated by Southern Shorthaul Railroad.

Last sighted 3rd January 2020 idle trailing RL305 and BRM002,

leading 48 grain hoppers, Barwon Park loop, Inverleigh. G514, named 'Graham Cotterall', now features "Southern Shorthaul Railroad's"

'black and yellow' livery. It is owned and operated by Southern Shorthaul Railroad.

Last sighted 9th May 2016 Down Freight trailing SSR101 and SSR002,

leading 45 empty grain hoppers, passing through Breeza (NSW). G515 now features "Rail First Asset Management's" 'blue, grey and yellow' livery.

It is owned by Rail First Asset Management and leased to QUBE Logistics.

Last sighted 24th May 2024 Down Freight trailing VL357, leading

23 container flats and 14 empty flats, passing through Clunes. G516 now features "Linx Cargo Care Group's" 'black, blue and white' livery

(not pictured). It is now owned and operated by Linx Cargo Care Group.

Last sighted 11th May 2016 Up Freight trailing LDP001 and LDP002,

leading SCT vans and container/flats, passing through East Maitland (NSW). G517 is no longer in service. On the 26th November 1999, G517

hauling grain, was routed into Ararat and collided with stationary G518

hauling ballast at more than 70 km/h. It was subsequently scrapped.

Photo courtesy Frank Hinde. G518 is no longer in service. On the 26th November 1999, G518

hauling ballast stationary at Ararat, was hit by G517 hauling grain

at more than 70 km/h. It was subsequently scrapped.

Photo courtesy Pete Perry. G520 still features "Freight Australia" 'green and yellow' livery however the

'Freight Australia' logos have been covered with 'Pacific National' logos.

Last sighted 7th August 2024 Up Freight, leading G540

and 59 container flats, passing through Gnarkeet. G521 now features "QUBE Logistic's" 'grey

and yellow' livery. It is owned by QUBE Logistics.

Last sighted 4th July 2023 Down Freight trailing

G512, leading 34 container flats, passing through Clunes. G523 still features "Freight Australia" 'green and yellow' livery however the

'Freight Australia' logos have been covered with 'Pacific National' logos.

Last sighted 2nd August 2024 Up Freight trailing G540, leading

G520 and 72 container flats, passing through Werneth. G524 still features "Freight Australia" 'green and yellow' livery however the

'Freight Australia' logos have been covered with 'Pacific National' logos.

Last sighted 28th April 2024 Down Freight, leading G536

and 39 empty grain hoppers, passing through Clunes. G526 still features "Freight Australia" 'green and yellow' livery however the

'Freight Australia' logos have been covered with 'Pacific National' logos.

Last sighted 21st June 2024 Down Freight trailing NR98 and NR31,

leading 71 container flat/wells, passing through Wal Wal. G528 still features "Freight Australia" 'green and yellow' livery however the

'Freight Australia' logos have been covered with 'Pacific National' logos.

Last sighted 5th November 2023 Up Freight trailing XR551, XR552,

XR555 and BL34, leading 40 grain hoppers, passing through Clunes. G532 now features "QUBE Logistic's" 'silver

and yellow' livery. It is owned by QUBE Logistics.

Last sighted 16th December 2022 Up Freight trailing G521,

leading 35 container flats and 1 empty flat, passing through Clunes. G533 now features "Aurizon" 'yellow' livery, still with remnents of

previous "Freightliner" 'green and yellow' livery. It is now owned by Aurizon.

Last sighted 5th July 2024 Up Freight trailing ACD6051, ACB4403, a crew car

and 28 container/flat/wells, leading 49 container/flat/wells, passing through Tatyoon. G534 now features "Linx Cargo Care Group's" 'black, blue and white' livery

(not pictured). It is now owned and operated by Linx Cargo Care Group.

Last sighted 5th May 2019 stabled, Goulburn

railway workshops yard sidings (NSW). G535 now features "Aurizon" 'yellow' livery, still with remnents of

previous "Freightliner" 'green and yellow' livery. It is now owned by Aurizon.

Last sighted 22nd June 2024 Down Freight trailing FQ02, ACD6047, a crew car, 29 container flat/

wells and ACB4403, leading 37 container/flat/wells and 12 empty flat/wells, departing Vite Vite loop. G537 still features "Freight Australia" 'green and yellow' livery however the

'Freight Australia' logos have been covered with 'Pacific National' logos.

Last sighted 27th October 2023 Down Freight trailing NR116, leading

NR97 and 67 container/flat/wells, passing through Langi Logan. G538 still features "Freight Australia" 'green and yellow' livery however the

'Freight Australia' logos have been covered with 'Pacific National' logos.

Last sighted 10th July 2024 Up Freight trailing NR83, leading NR57,

NR94 and 88 container flat/wells, passing through Langi Logan. G539 still features "Freight Australia" 'green and yellow' livery however the

'Freight Australia' logos have been covered with 'Pacific National' logos.

Last sighted 7th March 2024 Up Freight leading X48, G519

and 39 grain hoppers, passing through Langi Logan. G540, named 'Wycheproof', features "Pacific National's" 'blue and yellow'

livery, also with "Wakefield (Transport) 100 years" decals (not pictured).

Last sighted 7th August 2024 Up Freight trailing G520,

leading 59 container flats, passing through Gnarkeet. G542, named 'Warracknabeal', still features "Freight Australia" 'green and yellow' livery

however the 'Freight Australia' logos have been covered with 'Pacific National' logos.

Last sighted 23rd December 2022 stabled, latched

to 8121 and G538, Wurtun yard sidings (SA). H1 originally ordered as (the original) T413, is currently in storage in Seymour,

with the engine cladding removed and the engine partially tarped over.

Last sighted 6th December 2013 Down Freight, leading A78

and 20 empty ballast hoppers, passing through Wandong. H2 originally ordered as T414, features "Freight Australia" 'green and yellow'

livery however the 'Freight Australia' logos have been covered with 'Pacific

National' logos. It is now owned by Regional Connect. Last sighted 29th

April 2023 stabled latched behind T402, Seymour Railway Heritage Centre.
